Former Kenya Cup sides Mean Machine, Catholic Monks and Western Bulls are in pole position for a return to the top-flight league. Newbies Shamas Foundation and South Coast Pirates are also in the mix ahead of the last game of the regular season on Saturday. Two teams will be promoted to Kenya Cup to replace Kenya Harlequins and Nondies, who were relegated after finishing 11th and 12th in the top tier respectively. South Coast Pirates lead the Championship standings with 38 points from 10 games, two points clear of second-placed Shamas. Three-time Kenya Cup champions Mean Machine are third with 35 points. They fell 17-15 in a closely-fought encounter against Western Bulls while Catholic Monks are fourth with 34 points. Monks beat Egerton Wasps 13-10 over the weekend. Kakamega-based Bulls are fifth with 29 points and are also in the promotion mix. Bulls host former Kenya Cup side Kisumu RFC on Saturday at the Bull Ring in Kakamega while South Coast Pirates will travel to Nakuru for an encounter against Kabarak University. Shamas Foundation will be at home to Machine while Eldoret RFC will host USIU Martials at Eldoret Sports Club. University of Eldoretâ€™s Trojans will face relegation threatened Egerton Wasps in Eldoret as Catholic Monks battle Northern Suburbs.